{"id":271,"ayahs":[{"number":35,"arabic":"وَقَالَ ٱلَّذِينَ أَشْرَكُوا۟ لَوْ شَآءَ ٱللَّهُ مَا عَبَدْنَا مِن دُونِهِۦ مِن شَىْءٍۢ نَّحْنُ وَلَآ ءَابَآؤُنَا وَلَا حَرَّمْنَا مِن دُونِهِۦ مِن شَىْءٍۢ ۚ كَذَٰلِكَ فَعَلَ ٱلَّذِينَ مِن قَبْلِهِمْ ۚ فَهَلْ عَلَى ٱلرُّسُلِ إِلَّا ٱلْبَلَٰغُ ٱلْمُبِينُ","translation":"Now they who ascribe divinity to aught beside God say, \"Had God so willed, we would not have worshipped aught but Him - neither we nor our forefathers; nor would we have declared aught as forbidden without a commandment from Him.\" Even thus did speak those [sinners] who lived before their time; but, then, are the apostles bound to do more than clearly deliver the message [entrusted to them]?","audio":"https://cdn.islamic.network/quran/audio/128/ar.alafasy/1936.mp3","surahId":16,"words":[{"id":37660,"position":1,"arabic":"وَقَالَ","translation":"এবং বলে","audioUrl":"wbw/016_035_001.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":37661,"position":2,"arabic":"ٱلَّذِينَ","translation":"যারা","audioUrl":"wbw/016_035_002.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":37662,"position":3,"arabic":"أَشْرَكُوا۟","translation":"শিরক করেছে","audioUrl":"wbw/016_035_003.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":37663,"position":4,"arabic":"لَوْ","translation":"\"যদি","audioUrl":"wbw/016_035_004.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":37664,"position":5,"arabic":"شَآءَ","translation":"ইচ্ছে করতেন","audioUrl":"wbw/016_035_005.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":37665,"position":6,"arabic":"ٱللَّهُ","translation":"আল্লাহ্‌","audioUrl":"wbw/016_035_006.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":37666,"position":7,"arabic":"مَا","translation":"না","audioUrl":"wbw/016_035_007.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":37667,"position":8,"arabic":"عَبَدْنَا","translation":"আমরা ইবাদাত করতাম","audioUrl":"wbw/016_035_008.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":37668,"position":9,"arabic":"مِن","translation":"ছাড়া","audioUrl":"wbw/016_035_009.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":37669,"position":10,"arabic":"دُونِهِۦ","translation":"তাঁকে","audio